    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Q: What happens when there are "No More Moves"?</strong>
        <br>
        <strong>A:</strong> In Classic Mode, if the board reaches a state where no possible swaps can create a match, the game ends. In some versions, the game might automatically reshuffle the board for you.
    </p>
    <p>
        <strong>Q: What is the difference between Bejeweled Classic and Bejeweled Blitz?</strong>
        <br>
        <strong>A:</strong> Bejeweled Classic is a slower, more strategic, and untimed puzzle experience. Bejeweled Blitz is a fast-paced, 60-second competition where the goal is to get the highest score possible, often competing with friends on social media.
    </p>
